The defendant Ashley M. Hansen was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case Called @ 2:55 PM: Defendant Ashley M. Hansen in court, appearing pro se.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Def understands nature of State's motion.  Advised of right to counsel.  Def waives counsel today.  Def agrees she did not abide by terms of agreement.   Court accepts waiver of counsel and based upon Def's admission the agreement is set aside and JOC entered based upon prior NC plea.  Chapter 950 in compliance.  ADA makes statement as to sentencing.  Statement by Def:  None offered.  The Court:  30 days WCJ - I/S - Huber, GT and No TS credit.  S/W - 1 yr probation.  Conditions:  AODA and any follow thru; the defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician; Court Costs plus DNA Sample/Surcharge - 60 DTP or PP.  Right to expunge DNA record explained.  Appeal Rights Given.
